      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='black' class='header'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>NOT MAGIC?</font>, By Densel woshingtan of mith marr</b><br><br>I was reading all of the information of the almight fiery avenger and quickly noticed that the weapon wasn't listed as magic...that seems kinda odd to me considering it as the best paladin weapon in the game I would assume it would have at least every BASIC advantage. So I was wondering if the lack of being magic is correct. <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>SIR</font>, By Nitrus oxyde</b><br><br>The Fiery Avenger is, so far, the most powerful of the Holy Swords. This doesn't include the new Epic Quest item as we don't know what it is yet. This ought to give you a general idea of how to get it and what the quest involves. I won't swear by this, but many places on the internet can give better details. A man in the PoA named Inte Akira gives you the FA after the end of a LONG and HARD quest. If you are fortunate enough to see him, you can also see the FA as he is holding it. (Imagine a BIG soulfire.)#1. Give Inte a Ghoulbane and he gives you a note or testimony type deal. #2. Give Inte a Soulfire and he gives you another note or testimony. (I suggest you do this at the end of the quest, read on)#3. Kill Vox and Nagafen and get both rare drop halves of the book of scale. Give them and 1000pp to an NPC somewhere and he will combine them for you. You then trade this book for another. #4. Have someone charm a rare spawn NPC that is KOS to everyone. (From what I hear he resists it ALOT.) After this give him the book and he will disappear then immediately repop as a new NPC. I think its a lvl 55ish Necro or Shadow Knight. His name is Miraguil or something of the like. He drops his head and a robe. #5. Give the two testimony/note things, the head, and robe to Inte. Let sit for 15 minutes to rise and bake for 3 hours at 350 degrees. #6. Brag to all your friends about having a weapon that can theoretically do ~640 points of damage in one attack round. (THEORETICALLY... max str + double attacks that proc each time. So don't complain if I did the math wrong.)<P>

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
